org.python.modules

Class itertools

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.python.modules.itertools
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ClassDictInit

    public class itertools
extends Object
implements ClassDictInit
    Functional tools for creating and using iterators. Java implementation of the CPython module itertools.
    Since:
    2.5

        public static PyIterator imap(PyObject[] argstar)

      • islice

        public static PyIterator islice(PyObject iterable,
                PyObject startObj,
                PyObject stopObj,
                PyObject stepObj)
        Creates an iterator that returns selected values from an iterable.
        Parameters:
        startObj - the index of where in the iterable to start returning values
        stopObj - the index of where in the iterable to stop returning values
        stepObj - the number of steps to take beween each call to next()

      • islice

                PyObject stopObj)
        See Also:
        startObj defaults to 0 and stepObj to 1

      • ifilter

        public static PyIterator ifilter(PyObject predicate,
                 PyObject iterable)
        Creates an iterator that returns the items of the iterable for which predicate(item) is true. If predicate is null (None) return the items that are true.

      • ifilterfalse

        public static PyIterator ifilterfalse(PyObject predicate,
                      PyObject iterable)
        Creates an iterator that returns the items of the iterable for which predicate(item) is false. If predicate is null (None) return the items that are false.

      • izip

        public static PyIterator izip(PyObject[] argstar)
        Create an iterator whose next() method returns a tuple where the i-th element comes from the i-th iterable argument. Continues until the shortest iterable is exhausted. (Code in this method is based on __builtin__.zip()).

      • starmap

        public static PyIterator starmap(PyObject[] starargs)
        Create an iterator whose next() method returns the result of calling the function (first argument) with a tuple of arguments returned from the iterable (second argument).
        Parameters:
        starargs - [0] = callable function, [1] = iterable with argument tuples

      • dropwhile

        public static PyIterator dropwhile(PyObject predicate,
                   PyObject iterable)
        Create an iterator that drops items from the iterable while prdicate(item) equals true. After which every remaining item of the iterable is returned.

      • takewhile

        public static PyIterator takewhile(PyObject predicate,
                   PyObject iterable)
        Create an iterator that returns items from the iterable while predicate(item) is true. After which iteration is stopped.

      • groupby

        public static PyIterator groupby(PyObject[] args,
                 String[] kws)
        Create an iterator which returns the pair (key, sub-iterator) grouped by key(value).
